                        <summary><title type="uniform" xml:lang="en">The Revelations of St Birgitta
                                of Sweden</title>
                            <title type="uniform" xml:lang="la">Revelationes sancte
                            Birgitte</title>. Dating from the second half of the fifteenth century
                            the fragments that comprise <ref>AM 1056 4to</ref> are some of the few
                            extant translations into Old Danish from Latin of St Birgitta of
                            Sweden's 'Book of Revelations' ('Liber Celestis Reuelacionum'). The
                            other fragments of St Birgitta's 'Revelations' in Old Danish are: <ref type="ms" target="#AM08-0079-I-gamma-en">AM 79 I γ 8vo</ref>;
                                <ref>The National Archives of Norway, No. 84</ref>, and <ref>Danish
                                National Archives, E 338</ref>.</summary>
